🚀 SECTION 6: DYNAMIC PROGRAMMING (DP)
🧠 What is Dynamic Programming?
Dynamic Programming is a technique used to:

Solve complex problems

By breaking them into smaller subproblems

And storing results to avoid recomputation

⚡ Key Idea
👉 Overlapping Subproblems + Optimal Substructure

🔑 Two Main Approaches
1. 🧾 Memoization (Top-Down)
Recursion + caching

2. 📊 Tabulation (Bottom-Up)
Iterative + DP table

🧠 Example Concept (Fibonacci)
Instead of:

fib(5) = fib(4) + fib(3)
We store:

dp[5] = dp[4] + dp[3]
⚠️ Important Interview Points
Identify DP problems:

Repeated calculations

Min / Max / Count problems

Always think:
👉 “Can I reuse previous results?”

